@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - streaming/Stream
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Stream spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetStream;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListStreams using filters compartment_id, id,\nname, state (+1 more);
:Create the OCI resource via CreateStream when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteStream with best-effort\nvia GetStream or ListStreams to DELETED\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetStream or ListStreams\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
:Delete owned Secret side effects only after\nOCI delete confirmation;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields name, partitions, retention_in_hours\nand conflicts compartment_id ->\nstream_pool_id, stream_pool_id ->\ncompartment_id;
stop
endif
:Enforce conflictsWith rules compartment_id ->\nstream_pool_id, stream_pool_id ->\ncompartment_id before any OCI mutation;
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeStreamCompartment, UpdateStream\nonly for mutable fields compartment_id,\ndefined_tags, freeform_tags, stream_pool_id;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForUpdatedState;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply repo-authored secret policy ready-only\nwrites after ACTIVE;
if ("Secret sync succeeds?") then (yes)
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
else (no)
:Block successful completion until Secret sync\nsucceeds;
endif
:Project manual status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
:Keep promotion blocked on bind-versus-create,\ndelete-confirmation, endpoint-materialization,\nlegacy-adapter, list-lookup (+2 more);
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Legacy-adapter controllers
specialize the shared reconcile path while
explicit gaps still block generated promotion.
service: streaming
slug: stream
kind: Stream
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: compartment_id, defined_tags,
freeform_tags, stream_pool_id
reject before mutate: force-new fields name,
partitions, retention_in_hours and conflicts
compartment_id -> stream_pool_id, stream_pool_id
-> compartment_id
list lookup: oci_streaming_streams filters
compartment_id, id, name, state (+1 more)
conflicts: compartment_id -> stream_pool_id,
stream_pool_id -> compartment_id
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, endpoint-materialization,
legacy-adapter, list-lookup (+2 more)
Create or bind selection depends on name-based
list lookup with optional pool and compartment
filters.
Endpoint secret materialization happens only
after ACTIVE.
Delete is best-effort today; DELETING is treated
as sufficient for cleanup and finalizer removal.
end note
@enduml
